## Delite Blockchain

** chain-id: delite_22-1 **

Delite Blockchain 2022 testnet #1

**4 validator nodes:**

delite1 10.10.0.61

delite2 10.10.0.249

delite3 10.10.0.151

delite4 10.10.0.34

### Compile Delite Blockchain node and join the network: 

1) Install gcc, make, go v1.7

2) Clone repo

3) cd into repo directory and
   
   $ make install

4) add to ~/.profile: 
```   
   /home/<username>/go/bin/delited
```   
   $ source ~/.profile

5) $ delited 
   
   shows delited help info

6) $ delited init <choose a node name> --chain-id delite_22-1

7) change directory to:  ~/.delited/config

8) $ rm genesis.json

9) create a new file: genesis.json
   
   copy GENESIS_APR1.JSON content to new genesis.json and save

10) Edit ~/.delited/config/config.toml file:
    
    a) set persistent_peers to "afcbea1fa28457ec8c13128eb9a18066ff514216@10.10.0.61:26656,f20ae472745cee72d7125fe9bf68f26ccce1388d@10.10.0.249:26656,368b6d6ee4164311d1c6096be46b93175af4c380@10.10.0.151:26656,1cf0c06b00d9ce3dddee4db2bd074922fce4b05f@10.10.0.34:26656"
    
    b) RPC Server Configuration Options: change laddr="tcp://127.0.0.1:26657" to laddr="tcp://0.0.0.0:26657"

11) $ delited start

12) Delite Blockchain node starts joining the blockchain network and syncing to the latest block

** Create account and get test tokens: **

$ delited keys add <choose an account name>

Set account password - enter twice 

Record new account information print-out for future reference




